Candidates (any order, user picks):
----------------------------------------------------------------------

(a) forgot-password tRPC procedure         [pairs with auth.register]
    Scope: Tier 2 (~6 files)
    - apps/web/src/server/trpc/routers/auth.ts — add `requestPasswordReset` + `resetPassword`
    - packages/shared/src/schemas/auth.ts — add request/reset input schemas
    - apps/web/src/server/lib/email.ts — new SMTP wrapper (deferred actual delivery test)
    - apps/web/src/app/(auth)/forgot-password/page.tsx — wire form to mutation (RHF + shadcn Form per UI Rule #4)
    - apps/web/src/app/(auth)/reset-password/[token]/page.tsx — token consumer
    - auth.test.ts: 3+ test cases (request issues token, invalid token rejected, valid token resets + invalidates session)
    Blocker: SMTP credentials ⏳ — email delivery itself untestable until filled
    Tests: mock @yelli/db + mocked SMTP transport (nodemailer) for unit coverage
    Bonus: now that shadcn Form is wired (Phase 7 #3), forgot-password forms can reuse the same pattern as meetings/new

(c) JWT org-slug encoding                   [middleware foundation — high-risk]
    Scope: Tier 3 (~10 files, middleware + auth.config + session callback + all consumers)
    - apps/web/src/server/auth.config.ts — add `organization_slug` to JWT
    - apps/web/src/server/auth.ts — populate from session.user
    - apps/web/src/middleware.ts — resolve tenant from JWT, validate URL ↔ session match (security.md TENANT MIDDLEWARE SAFETY)
    - Test: middleware unit test for tenant-switch attack rejection
    Risk: every authenticated route depends on this; reserve for careful fresh-context session
    Tier 3 → mandatory split via memory-governance §1: probably 3 sub-sessions (auth.config + auth.ts → middleware → consumers).

(d) join/[token] tRPC                       [needs LiveKit ⏳ for full integration]
    Unit tests OK against mocked LiveKit token mint; integration deferred until LIVEKIT_API_KEY filled
    Existing getJoinToken in meetingsRouter has 0 test coverage — could pair with this if scope allows

(e) Socket.IO auth middleware               [depends on (c)]
    Should land AFTER (c) so the JWT contract is stable

(f) Root landing page                       [verify scope first]
    Current /page.tsx is 11 lines — check PRODUCT.md for what's expected
    Likely Tier 1

(g) Coverage threshold gate                 [housekeeping — ~1 file]
    `vitest run --coverage` works (12 tests cover authRouter.register + meetingsRouter.create)
    No minimum % gate yet — add to vitest.config.ts and CI workflow
    Should land before Phase 8 — quick win to lock the safety net

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Rule 25 reminder for ALL of the above:
  → Write failing test FIRST (RED), then implementation (GREEN), then refactor.
  → Test patterns: [[trpc-test-pattern]] (Phase 7 #2) + [[meetings-protected-route-test]] (Phase 7 #3).
  → For forms: reuse the [[shadcn-form-primitive]] pattern from Phase 7 #3 (`_meeting-form.tsx` as reference impl).
  → For shared schemas: `<Entity>CreateClientInputSchema` for client-facing input, `<Entity>CreateInputSchema` for admin/internal projection.

Recommended next: (a) forgot-password — closes the auth quartet (register ✓, password reset, login ✓, logout). Reuses meetings/new RHF pattern. SMTP unit tests via mocked transport unblock the work even while SMTP credentials remain ⏳.

Pending Rule 16 follow-up: smoke-test /app/meetings/new in browser after next `pnpm dev` up. The RHF refactor is unit-test + build covered but the actual page render under SSR + hydration hasn't been verified in a logged-in session.
